  "prompt": "What are the best questions to ask people to evoke wisdom?",
  "response": "Here are some thought-provoking questions that can help elicit deeper insights and wisdom:\n\n1. Personal Reflection Questions:\n- What's the most important lesson life has taught you?\n- What advice would you give your younger self?\n- What do you know now that you wish you'd understood earlier?\n\n2. Learning and Growth Questions:\n- What experience fundamentally changed your perspective?\n- How have your biggest failures shaped who you are today?\n- What's something you've unlearned that used to be important to you?\n\n3. Philosophical Questions:\n- What does a meaningful life look like to you?\n- How do you define success beyond traditional metrics?\n- What do you believe is the purpose of human existence?\n\n4. Empathy and Understanding Questions:\n- What's something most people don't understand about you?\n- When have you felt most connected to others?\n- What helps you maintain compassion during difficult times?\n\n5. Wisdom-Oriented Questions:\n- What principles guide your most important decisions?\n- How do you balance practicality with idealism?\n- What have you learned about human nature?\n\nThe key is asking with genuine curiosity, listening actively, and creating a safe space for authentic reflection.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these?",
